WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:03.667
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.667 --> 00:06.300
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.300 --> 00:10.500
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.500 --> 00:12.600
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.600 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:15.834
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:15.834 --> 00:18.734
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.734 --> 00:22.500
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:22.500 --> 00:24.200
HE REALLY
TAKES THIS SERIOUSLY.

00:24.200 --> 00:25.567
OH, HE'S A BIRTHDAY FREAK.

00:25.567 --> 00:27.500
I CAN'T TAKE
THIS PRESSURE EVERY YEAR!

00:27.500 --> 00:29.600
I'M GONNA BE IN THERAPY
OVER THIS, AREN'T I?

00:29.600 --> 00:31.033
WE'LL GET A GROUP RATE.

00:31.033 --> 00:32.600
NOT GONNA HAPPEN!

00:32.600 --> 00:34.100
YOU HAVE WISELY CHOSEN
ERIC MATTHEWS

00:34.100 --> 00:35.967
AS THE "ALAN MATTHEWS
BIRTHDAY-PARTY PLANNER."

00:35.967 --> 00:37.500
BRAVO TO YOU.

00:37.500 --> 00:39.867
YOU ARE THE RIGHT MAN
FOR THE JOB, SWEETIE.

00:39.867 --> 00:41.500
YES, I AM!

00:41.500 --> 00:43.934
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.
HERE'S THE KEY AS I SEE IT.

00:43.934 --> 00:46.667
DAD WAS A NAVY MAN, WHICH MEANS
HE'LL USE ANY MEANS --

00:46.667 --> 00:49.233
EVEN TORTURE --
TO FIND OUT ABOUT THIS PARTY.

00:49.233 --> 00:51.400
DAD WAS A COOK
IN THE COAST GUARD.

00:51.400 --> 00:53.867
DADDY WAS A NAVY S.E.A.L.!

00:53.867 --> 00:55.767
DON'T YOU--

00:55.767 --> 00:57.500
MOM, MOM, MOM!

00:57.500 --> 00:58.734
HE'S DOING IT AGAIN!

00:58.734 --> 00:59.800
HI!

00:59.800 --> 01:00.834
HI!

01:00.834 --> 01:02.033
TELL HIM NOTHING!

01:03.133 --> 01:05.200
[ ERIC STOMPING ]

01:05.200 --> 01:07.800
AAH!

01:07.800 --> 01:09.500
THREE MORE DAYS.

01:09.500 --> 01:12.967
I'M GONNA BE<i>SO HAPPY</i>
IN THREE MORE DAYS.

01:12.967 --> 01:15.100
ANYBODY KNOW WHY?
HUH?

01:15.100 --> 01:16.734
MOR-R-R-GAN?

01:16.734 --> 01:18.867
I'M NOT PLAYIN'.

01:18.867 --> 01:22.600
WHAT...A...BABY!

01:22.600 --> 01:24.600
46. THE BIG 4-6.

01:24.600 --> 01:27.100
WHAT DO YOU GET
A 46-YEAR-OLD, HUH?

01:27.100 --> 01:28.734
ANYONE, ANYONE?

01:28.734 --> 01:31.500
OH, ALAN, LEAVE US
THE HELL ALONE.

01:31.500 --> 01:32.800
HEY!

01:32.800 --> 01:36.000
Cory: SHAWNIE! ANGELA!

01:36.000 --> 01:37.667
TELL THEM.

01:37.667 --> 01:39.600
TELL US WHAT?

01:39.600 --> 01:43.100
I GOT A LETTER
FROM MY MOM -- VIRNA.

01:43.100 --> 01:45.000
HAVE YOU OPENED IT?

01:45.000 --> 01:46.834
NO.
TEAR IT UP!

01:46.834 --> 01:49.200
I HAVEN'T HEARD FROM HER
IN THREE YEARS.

01:49.200 --> 01:51.000
HEY, SHAWN.

01:51.000 --> 01:52.300
HEY, MR. MATTHEWS!

01:52.300 --> 01:55.100
HAPPY BIRTHDAY
IN THREE DAYS, RIGHT? 46?

01:55.100 --> 01:57.867
THIS IS WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT, PEOPLE!

01:57.867 --> 01:59.400
THIS IS A GOOD BOY!

01:59.400 --> 02:03.467
SHAWN, LOOK. EVERYTHING'S
GOING GREAT FOR YOU.

02:03.467 --> 02:05.200
YOU'VE GOT FRIENDS.

02:05.200 --> 02:07.133
YOU'VE GOT A BEAUTIFUL,
HONEST, SWEET,

02:07.133 --> 02:08.667
LOVING WOMAN THAT LOVES YOU.

02:08.667 --> 02:10.600
THANKS, CORY.
SHUT UP!

02:10.600 --> 02:13.000
YOU'VE MADE PEACE
WITH YOUR FATHER'S DEATH.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.100
YOU'VE MADE PEACE
WITH YOUR LOONY MOTHER.

02:15.100 --> 02:17.000
THERE'S<i>NO </i>GOOD IN THAT LETTER.

02:17.000 --> 02:19.600
CORY, MAYBE SHAWN NEEDS
TO TAKE A LOOK AT THAT LETTER

02:19.600 --> 02:21.600
FOR REASONS
YOU CAN'T SEE RIGHT NOW.

02:21.600 --> 02:25.200
GEE, MOM, I'M -- I'M LOOKING
AROUND THE ROOM HERE,

02:25.200 --> 02:28.200
TRYING TO SEE
IF ANYONE ASKED YOUR OPINION.

02:28.200 --> 02:32.233
I DON'T SEE ANYONE.
IS ANYONE -- NO?

02:32.233 --> 02:37.767
LOOK, YOU WANT AN OPINION,
YOU ASK TOPANGA, OKAY?

02:37.767 --> 02:41.100
ASK HER! GO AHEAD.
TOPANGA, TELL HIM.

02:41.100 --> 02:43.867
I THINK YOU NEED
TO LET SHAWN

02:43.867 --> 02:45.900
DO WHATEVER HE WANTS.

02:45.900 --> 02:47.767
[ CHUCKLES ] EXCUSE ME.

02:47.767 --> 02:51.767
DON'T YOU EVER SNAP AT ME
LIKE THAT IN PUBLIC AGAIN!

02:53.867 --> 02:56.600
IT SAYS MY MOM
IS SOMEWHERE IN HONDURAS...

02:56.600 --> 02:58.834
OH, NO!
HE OPENED IT.

02:58.834 --> 03:01.400
AND SHE'S NEVER COMING BACK.
THAT'S NOTHING NEW.

03:01.400 --> 03:02.800
SHE HEARD THAT DAD DIED,

03:02.800 --> 03:05.400
AND NOW I HAVE THE RIGHT
TO KNOW SOMETHING.

03:05.400 --> 03:07.600
SHAWN, PUT THE LETTER
BACK IN THE ENVELOPE!

03:07.600 --> 03:09.500
WAIT A MINUTE!
MAYBE IT'S GOOD NEWS.

03:09.500 --> 03:10.500
TRUST ME!
IT'S NOT!

03:12.000 --> 03:13.133
SHAWN...

03:13.133 --> 03:15.700
SHE'S NOT MY REAL MOTHER.

03:26.000 --> 03:28.300
WE GOTTA FIND MY MOM, JACK.
SHE'S THE ONLY...

03:28.300 --> 03:29.834
FAMILY YOU HAVE LEFT?

03:29.834 --> 03:32.667
LET'S GO ON A SEARCH
FOR YOUR BROTHER.

03:32.667 --> 03:34.900
WAIT A MINUTE!
WE DON'T HAVE TO. HE'S HERE.

03:34.900 --> 03:36.934
YOU'RE MY HALF BROTHER.

03:36.934 --> 03:39.967
HOW ABOUT THE OTHER HALF
BEATS THE CRAP OUT OF YOU?

03:39.967 --> 03:42.700
OKAY!
LISTEN UP, PEOPLE.

03:42.700 --> 03:45.500
HERE'S THE PLAN
AS I SEE IT.

03:49.000 --> 03:51.800
WE GIVE MORGAN,
WHO WILL BE OUR DECOY,

03:51.800 --> 03:54.900
SOME KIND OF POISON
THAT WILL MAKE HER ILL.

03:54.900 --> 03:57.967
DAD WILL HAVE TO TAKE HER
TO THE HOSPITAL,

03:57.967 --> 04:00.600
AND WHEN HE'S
IN THE EMERGENCY ROOM,

04:00.600 --> 04:02.600
<i>THAT'S </i>WHEN THE PARTY BEGINS.

04:02.600 --> 04:05.200
SO, LET ME MAKE SURE
I UNDERSTAND THIS.

04:05.200 --> 04:07.500
YOU'RE WILLING
TO POISON YOUR SISTER

04:07.500 --> 04:08.967
TO SURPRISE YOUR FATHER.

04:08.967 --> 04:12.500
THE PROBLEM IS,
IF MORGAN GOES SOUTH,

04:12.500 --> 04:16.500
I MEAN, IF SHE,
ACTUALLY, WELL, CROAKS...

04:16.500 --> 04:20.767
IT'S GONNA PUT A DAMPER
ON THE ENTIRE PARTY...

04:20.767 --> 04:24.300
WHICH IS WHY WE GET
HORSEY RIDES!

04:25.400 --> 04:26.834
NOTICE ME.

04:26.834 --> 04:30.233
I'M ERIC, ON THE HORSEY --
LET'S CALL HIM PETE.

04:30.233 --> 04:32.934
THE TWO OF US TOGETHER,

04:32.934 --> 04:36.467
HAVING FUN, JOY,
MERRIMENT.

04:36.467 --> 04:37.834
CORY.

04:37.834 --> 04:39.200
I WANNA BE
OVER THERE NOW.

04:39.200 --> 04:40.367
TAKE ME WITH YOU!

04:40.367 --> 04:42.700
ALL RIGHT,
IF ANY OF YOU NEED ME,

04:42.700 --> 04:45.000
I'M GONNA BE
AT THE POISON STORE.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.000
INTERESTING FAMILY
ON DAD'S SIDE.

04:47.000 --> 04:49.367
HIS GREAT-GRANDFATHER
AND GREAT-UNCLE

04:49.367 --> 04:50.734
WERE BORN IN SCOTLAND.

04:50.734 --> 04:53.400
Together:
AH! SCOTTISH.

04:53.400 --> 04:55.700
AND WHAT THEY WERE KNOWN FOR
WAS, WELL,

04:55.700 --> 04:58.500
ONE DAY, THEY SLAUGHTERED
THEIR ENTIRE VILLAGE.

04:58.500 --> 05:01.600
Together:
AH! SLAUGHTERERS.

05:01.600 --> 05:04.200
I COME FROM THIEVES
AND PILLAGERS.

05:04.200 --> 05:06.100
I COME FROM BAD PEOPLE.

05:06.100 --> 05:08.133
YOU KNOW, WE HAVEN'T
LOOKED UP YOUR MOM'S SIDE.

05:08.133 --> 05:09.900
I'VE HAD THREE MOTHERS.

05:09.900 --> 05:13.400
YES, UH, VIRNA, MING WA,
AND ELAINE.

05:13.400 --> 05:15.967
I THINK
WE CAN RULE MING WA OUT.

05:15.967 --> 05:18.300
HMM.
WHICH LEAVES ELAINE.

05:18.300 --> 05:22.567
ELAINE McGINTY. AH, YES.
LAST SPOTTED IN BOSTON.

05:22.567 --> 05:24.600
SHE'S PROBABLY
SITTING IN A COFFEEHOUSE,

05:24.600 --> 05:26.200
READING POETRY RIGHT NOW.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.600
YOU THINK ELAINE'S WHERE I GOT
MY POETRY THING, COR?

05:28.600 --> 05:31.567
NO.
WHY NOT?

05:31.567 --> 05:34.000
I JUST DON'T WANT YOU
TO EXPECT ANYTHING.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.133
OKAY...I'VE ENTERED
ALL THE INFORMATION,

05:36.133 --> 05:38.500
SO ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS HIT "SEARCH,"

05:38.500 --> 05:41.734
AND THEY'LL SEND YOU THE RESULTS
A FEW DAYS LATER IN THE MAIL.

05:41.734 --> 05:43.734
SURE YOU WANT TO DO THIS, RIGHT?

05:43.734 --> 05:46.467
OH, I'M SURE!

05:46.467 --> 05:49.700
IS THAT
YOUR FINAL ANSWER?

05:49.700 --> 05:50.600
YEAH.

05:58.033 --> 06:00.934
OKAY, SO WHEN
THE FIRECRACKERS GO OFF,

06:00.934 --> 06:03.233
RACHEL RUNS INSIDE THE HOUSE
AND YELLS...

06:03.233 --> 06:05.400
"THE JAPANESE
ARE ATTACKING.

06:05.400 --> 06:07.467
THE JAPANESE
ARE ATTACKING."

06:09.367 --> 06:10.900
WOW.

06:10.900 --> 06:13.767
OKAY, UM, SEE,
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU!

06:13.767 --> 06:15.100
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

06:15.100 --> 06:18.000
DADDY WILL RUN OUTSIDE!
HE'S A NAVY S.E.A.L.!

06:18.000 --> 06:19.000
NOT!

06:19.000 --> 06:20.233
SHUT!

06:20.233 --> 06:22.700
YOU, YOU!
YOU GOTTA GET YOUR CAKES!

06:22.700 --> 06:25.300
THAT'S THE<i>ONLY </i>JOB,
IS TO GET THE CAKES!

06:25.300 --> 06:26.734
YOU GOT THAT, SQUIRT?

06:26.734 --> 06:28.233
I LIKE WHEN
YOU CALL ME "SQUIRT."

06:29.800 --> 06:31.367
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY!

06:31.367 --> 06:32.934
I HOLD IN MY HAND

06:32.934 --> 06:36.300
THE RESEARCH RESULT
OF ONE ELAINE McGINTY HUNTER.

06:36.300 --> 06:38.667
I HAVE A MOTHER!
SHE'S IN HERE.

06:38.667 --> 06:40.000
OPEN IT!

06:40.000 --> 06:41.200
YEAH, OPEN IT,

06:41.200 --> 06:42.934
BECAUSE THINGS
ARE GOING GREAT.

06:42.934 --> 06:44.800
EVERYBODY'S HAPPY,
WE'RE ALL GETTING ALONG,

06:44.800 --> 06:45.800
AND WHO WANTS THAT?

06:45.800 --> 06:47.000
WHAT?

06:47.000 --> 06:48.867
YEAH! OPEN IT.

06:48.867 --> 06:51.667
[ SIGHS ]

06:51.667 --> 06:52.967
HUH.
HOW ABOUT THAT?

06:52.967 --> 06:54.800
THESE HUNTERS
ARE TRICKY PEOPLE.

06:54.800 --> 06:56.133
IT MUST BE IN OUR BLOOD.

06:56.133 --> 06:58.300
IF A HUNTER DOESN'T
WANT TO BE FOUND,

06:58.300 --> 06:59.600
SHE WON'T BE FOUND.

06:59.600 --> 07:01.667
YOU KNOW, MAYBE WE CAN
JUST TRY AGAIN.

07:01.667 --> 07:04.033
NO, NO, BECAUSE EVERY TRACE
THAT WE DID, JACK,

07:04.033 --> 07:05.200
THEY CAME UP EMPTY.

07:05.200 --> 07:06.600
MAYBE SHE GOT MARRIED AGAIN.

07:06.600 --> 07:08.400
MAYBE HER NAME
JUST CHANGED.

07:08.400 --> 07:10.600
MAYBE SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO BE FOUND.

07:10.600 --> 07:13.000
MAYBE SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO BE FOUND BY ME.

07:13.000 --> 07:14.400
YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

07:14.400 --> 07:16.200
Rachel:
ARE YOU OKAY?

07:16.200 --> 07:19.100
NO -- YEAH, I'M FINE.
I KNEW THIS WAS A LONG SHOT.

07:19.100 --> 07:21.500
I'M JUST, YOU KNOW --
I'M GLAD THAT I TRIED.

07:21.500 --> 07:25.000
SHAWN, YOU HAVE A TENDENCY
TO PUSH YOUR FRIENDS AWAY

07:25.000 --> 07:27.300
WHEN THESE THINGS
HAPPEN TO YOU.

07:27.300 --> 07:29.200
SHAWN,
WE'RE HAPPY NOW, OKAY?

07:29.200 --> 07:32.300
DON'T YOU DARE GO
DOING SOMETHING CRAZY TO US.

07:32.300 --> 07:33.500
ANGELA.
LOVE. KISS.

07:33.500 --> 07:35.200
[ New York accent ]
FORGET ABOUT IT!

07:35.200 --> 07:38.000
OKAY.
I'M LEAVING NOW.

07:38.000 --> 07:39.467
NOT SOME BIG SHAWN EXIT.

07:39.467 --> 07:41.400
I JUST GOT
STUFF TO DO, OKAY?

07:41.400 --> 07:43.400
GO ON!
GET OUTTA HERE!

07:43.400 --> 07:45.133
WE'RE TIRED OF LOOKING
AT YOUR UGLY FACE, RIGHT?

07:45.133 --> 07:46.500
GET OUT!
LEAVE! GET OUT!

07:46.500 --> 07:49.967
DON'T FORGET
ABOUT MY DAD'S PARTY, OKAY?

07:49.967 --> 07:51.400
WOULDN'T MISS IT.

07:54.133 --> 07:55.133
CORY?

07:55.133 --> 07:56.467
YEAH?

07:56.467 --> 07:58.400
WHAT DO YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA DO?

07:58.400 --> 08:01.200
PROBABLY SOMETHING
THAT WILL DEVASTATE HIMSELF,

08:01.200 --> 08:03.233
AS WELL AS
EVERYONE AROUND HIM.

08:03.233 --> 08:05.867
THE USUAL.

08:12.600 --> 08:14.200
HEY, DADDY-O.

08:14.200 --> 08:16.000
[ Depressed ] HI.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.400
YOU ALL SAD?

08:17.400 --> 08:18.600
YEAH.

08:18.600 --> 08:19.967
'CAUSE IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY,

08:19.967 --> 08:21.934
SO YOU DIDN'T MAKE ANY PLANS
SO YOU COULD BE HERE,

08:21.934 --> 08:23.400
AND NOW
NOBODY'S DOING ANYTHING?

08:23.400 --> 08:24.600
YEAH.

08:24.600 --> 08:26.967
YEAH?

08:26.967 --> 08:29.800
WELL, YOU DIDN'T MAKE
ANY PLANS FOR...

08:29.800 --> 08:32.400
TOMORROW NIGHT, DID YOU?

08:32.400 --> 08:34.734
WHY?

08:34.734 --> 08:35.867
OH, NO!
THERE'S NO REASON.

08:35.867 --> 08:37.133
NO REASON AT ALL.

08:37.133 --> 08:38.834
I JUST DON'T WANT YOU
TO MAKE ANY PLANS FOR...

08:38.834 --> 08:40.000
<i>TOMORROW </i>NIGHT.

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
TELL ME.
NO, I CAN'T.

08:42.000 --> 08:43.200
TELL ME.
I CAN'T TELL.

08:43.200 --> 08:44.700
TELL ME.
AH-HA! HA! HA!

08:44.700 --> 08:46.300
TELL ME.
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

08:46.300 --> 08:48.400
[ Laughing ]
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY!

08:48.400 --> 08:50.300
BIG BASH!
BIG LUAU, OKAY?

08:50.300 --> 08:52.100
TOMORROW NIGHT?

08:52.100 --> 08:54.300
BUT TOMORROW NIGHT'S
NOT MY BIRTHDAY!

08:54.300 --> 08:56.400
TOMORROW NIGHT'S
JUST TOMORROW NIGHT!

08:56.400 --> 08:58.767
I HAVE A HORSEY COMING.

08:58.767 --> 09:01.667
ERIC, YOU THROW
A BIRTHDAY PARTY

09:01.667 --> 09:03.600
<i>ON </i>A PERSON'S BIRTHDAY!

09:03.600 --> 09:06.000
THEN YOU'RE NOT
GONNA BE SURPRISED! HI!

09:06.000 --> 09:08.900
I THINK I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING,
ALL RIGHT, DAD?

09:08.900 --> 09:10.967
I'VE PLANNED
THIS WHOLE THING MYSELF.

09:13.400 --> 09:17.600
YOU KNOW, SO, LIKE,
HOW MUCH DO YOU LIKE MORGAN?

09:17.600 --> 09:21.000
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
HERE, NOW?

09:21.000 --> 09:23.033
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY.
I DON'T KNOW.

09:23.033 --> 09:26.133
MOM TOLD ME TO BE HERE
AT EXACTLY 7:30 FOR SOMETHING.

09:27.734 --> 09:31.233
SURPRISE!
SURPRISE!

09:31.233 --> 09:32.233
WHOA!

09:32.233 --> 09:33.500
OUTSTANDING!

09:33.500 --> 09:35.200
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?!

09:35.200 --> 09:37.800
OH, ERIC,
WE USED YOU AS A DECOY.

09:37.800 --> 09:41.567
WE KNEW YOU'D BE STUPID,
SO WE USED IT AGAINST YOU.

09:41.567 --> 09:44.300
[ Laughing ] I WAS THE DECOY
'CAUSE I'M SO STUPID!

09:44.300 --> 09:46.734
I AM SO STUPID,
BUT YOU KNOW SOMETHING?

09:46.734 --> 09:49.033
THAT'S GONNA MAKE MY PARTY
FOR YOU TOMORROW

09:49.033 --> 09:51.100
A<i>BIG </i>SURPRISE,
RIGHT, DAD?

09:51.100 --> 09:52.834
RIGHT!

09:52.834 --> 09:54.000
[ LAUGHS ]

09:54.000 --> 09:55.567
[ DOOR OPENS ]

09:55.567 --> 09:57.000
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:57.000 --> 09:58.800
SURPRISE!

09:58.800 --> 10:01.100
It's tomorrow night,
you idiot!

10:01.100 --> 10:02.133
HEY, SHAWN!

10:02.133 --> 10:03.867
All:
HEY, SHAWN!

10:03.867 --> 10:06.033
HAPPY BIRTHDAY,
CORY'S FATHER.

10:06.033 --> 10:07.500
SHAWN, COULD I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

10:07.500 --> 10:09.133
I JUST WANT TO TALK TO YOU
FOR ONE SECOND.

10:09.133 --> 10:10.867
I DON'T WANNA
TALK TO YOU.

10:10.867 --> 10:13.300
YEAH. OKAY.

10:13.300 --> 10:15.367
OH, BOY.

10:15.367 --> 10:18.567
SHAWN, BABY.
UM...YOU ALL RIGHT?

10:18.567 --> 10:20.600
YEAH, I'M FINE, BABY.
HOW ARE YOU?

10:20.600 --> 10:22.867
IT'S A PLEASURE
TO SEE YOU THIS EVENING.

10:22.867 --> 10:23.900
YOU LOOK GREAT.

10:23.900 --> 10:25.767
SHAWN...

10:25.767 --> 10:29.500
WHAT?
YOU DISAPPOINTED?

10:29.500 --> 10:31.133
SHE'S DISAPPOINTED.

10:31.133 --> 10:33.367
DUDE!
[ Mocking Jack ]
DUDE!

10:33.367 --> 10:35.367
SHAWN...
SHAWN!

10:35.367 --> 10:38.000
AW, COME ON, MAN!
AW, COME ON, MAN!

10:38.000 --> 10:39.500
MAN, BUDDY, SHAWN,
HEY, HEY!

10:39.500 --> 10:40.934
HEY, HEY! WHOA, WHOA!
HEY!

10:40.934 --> 10:42.133
HEY!
HEY!

10:42.133 --> 10:43.600
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE DRINKING, RIGHT?

10:43.600 --> 10:47.200
SHAWN, YOU KNOW WHAT?
LET'S JUST GO SIT TOGETHER.

10:47.200 --> 10:49.467
COME ON.
LET'S GO FOR A WALK.

10:49.467 --> 10:51.300
YOU STILL LOVE ME, HUH?

10:51.300 --> 10:52.467
YES.

10:52.467 --> 10:54.500
We don't have any mommies.

10:54.500 --> 10:56.300
I know.

10:57.900 --> 11:00.300
WHY DON'T YOU COME INTO
THE KITCHEN FOR A MINUTE?

11:00.300 --> 11:02.200
YOU GONNA MAKE ME AN OMELET?

11:02.200 --> 11:04.367
I WANT TO HAVE
A TALK WITH YOU. NOW.

11:04.367 --> 11:06.500
[ Under his breath ]
YOU'RE NOT MY DAD.

11:06.500 --> 11:07.967
I'M ALL YOU HAVE --

11:07.967 --> 11:10.367
WAIT, WHA--
YOU'RE NOT MY DAD!

11:12.200 --> 11:14.400
I DON'T HAVE A DAD.

11:14.400 --> 11:17.033
AND I DON'T HAVE A MOM.

11:17.033 --> 11:20.900
I'M AN ORPHAN.
I'M AN OLD ORPHAN.

11:20.900 --> 11:22.900
MY CHILDHOOD IS OVER.

11:22.900 --> 11:27.900
AND I NEVER HAD...
ANY PARENTS.

11:27.900 --> 11:28.967
OH!

11:28.967 --> 11:32.200
GOD! STOP WHINING!

11:32.200 --> 11:36.467
I-I-I...hate you.

11:36.467 --> 11:39.600
I'LL BE YOUR FATHER.

11:39.600 --> 11:41.133
[ SNIFFS ]

11:41.133 --> 11:43.033
YOU'LL BE WHAT?

11:43.033 --> 11:45.800
I WANT YOU TO BE
A MEMBER OF THIS FAMILY.

11:45.800 --> 11:47.700
ALAN?

11:47.700 --> 11:51.233
<i>WE </i>WANT YOU TO BE
A MEMBER OF THIS FAMILY.

11:52.900 --> 11:54.467
YEAH, WE DO.

11:54.467 --> 11:58.600
YOU NEED A MOM?
I'M A REALLY GOOD MOM.

11:58.600 --> 12:00.734
I GOT REFERENCES.

12:00.734 --> 12:02.467
YEAH, SHE'S GOOD.

12:02.467 --> 12:05.100
SHE'S THE BEST
I'VE EVER HAD.

12:09.934 --> 12:12.667
DO YOU WANT TO ADOPT ME?

12:12.667 --> 12:15.734
OH, SHAWN, YOU HAVE ALWAYS
BEEN A PART OF OUR FAMILY.

12:15.734 --> 12:17.967
HOW ABOUT
WE MAKE IT OFFICIAL?

12:17.967 --> 12:19.033
Yeah.

12:38.800 --> 12:42.100
[ SIGHS ] WELL, IT'S CORY
TO THE RESCUE.

12:42.100 --> 12:43.600
OLD FAITHFUL.

12:43.600 --> 12:45.300
WHY DON'T YOU
GO HOME TO YOUR WIFE

12:45.300 --> 12:47.033
AND LEAVE ME ALONE?

12:48.800 --> 12:51.133
SORRY, SANTA. I THOUGHT
YOU WERE SOMEONE ELSE.

12:51.133 --> 12:54.600
IT'S COLD OUT, SON.
GO HOME.

12:54.600 --> 12:58.000
WOW, HE REALLY
DIDN'T FOLLOW ME, HUH?

12:58.000 --> 13:02.467
MAN, A GUY GETS MARRIED,
AND THAT'S THE END OF ME.

13:08.700 --> 13:09.900
I'M HERE.

13:09.900 --> 13:11.967
I KNEW YOU WOULD BE.

13:11.967 --> 13:14.600
SO, WHERE WE GOING?

13:14.600 --> 13:17.100
I THOUGHT
WE'D GO TO THE CEMETERY.

13:17.100 --> 13:19.700
I THOUGHT
WE'D GO FOR PIE.

13:19.700 --> 13:21.467
CEMETERY.

13:21.467 --> 13:22.700
BOYSENBERRY.

13:22.700 --> 13:24.500
SHAWN, I DON'T LIKE
CEMETERIES.

13:24.500 --> 13:27.000
THERE'S A HIGH CONCENTRATION
OF DEAD PEOPLE.

13:27.000 --> 13:29.400
I HAVEN'T EVEN VISITED
MY NANA BOO BOO.

13:29.400 --> 13:31.500
YOUR NANA BOO BOO'S
NOT DEAD!

13:31.500 --> 13:33.567
OH, SO NOW
YOU'RE A DOCTOR?

13:33.567 --> 13:35.100
SHAWN! COME HERE.

13:35.100 --> 13:37.934
LOOK, COME BACK
TO MY HOUSE.

13:37.934 --> 13:40.567
OKAY, MY FAMILY OFFERED
TO ADOPT YOU TONIGHT.

13:40.567 --> 13:42.500
DO YOU KNOW
HOW GREAT THAT IS?

13:42.500 --> 13:44.500
YOU WOULD
ACTUALLY BE MY BROTHER.

13:44.500 --> 13:46.400
YOU<i>ARE </i>MY BROTHER ALREADY.

13:46.400 --> 13:48.100
SO COME BACK TO MY HOUSE.

13:48.100 --> 13:51.200
THERE'S<i>LIFE </i>AT MY HOUSE.
MY FAMILY WANTS YOU THERE.

13:51.200 --> 13:53.367
W-WHAT'S WAITING FOR YOU
AT THE CEMETERY?

13:53.367 --> 13:55.367
<i>MY </i>FAMILY.

13:55.367 --> 13:57.500
MINE.

14:11.033 --> 14:14.900
HEY! YOU HAVIN' A GOOD TIME
IN THERE WITH ALL YOUR SECRETS?

14:14.900 --> 14:17.834
LIKE THE FACT THAT
YOU'VE BEEN MARRIED 62 TIMES

14:17.834 --> 14:21.100
AND NEVER BOTHERED TO TELL ME
WHO MY REAL MOTHER WAS!

14:21.100 --> 14:23.734
WHAT POSSIBLE REASON
COULD A FATHER HAVE

14:23.734 --> 14:26.133
NOT TO TELL HIS BOY
WHO HIS MOM IS?!

14:26.133 --> 14:29.000
MAYBE THE FATHER WAS TRYIN'
TO PROTECT THE BOY.

14:32.133 --> 14:35.300
HEY, THANKS FOR
PLANTING THOSE FLOWERS THERE.

14:35.300 --> 14:38.100
YOU KEEP THE PLACE
REAL NICE AND PRETTY

14:38.100 --> 14:40.100
FOR ALL MY MANY VISITORS.

14:40.100 --> 14:42.700
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
WHO MY MOM WAS?

14:42.700 --> 14:44.000
YOUR MOTHER'S VIRNA.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.600
NO! THE WOMAN
WHO GAVE BIRTH TO ME.

14:46.600 --> 14:47.867
OH, HER.

14:47.867 --> 14:49.700
AH, SHE TOOK OFF.

14:49.700 --> 14:52.700
WHEN YOU WERE BORN,
I SAID,

14:52.700 --> 14:55.467
"HONEY, IT'S A --
HONEY?"

14:55.467 --> 14:58.667
[ CHUCKLES ]
BUT DON'T BLAME HER, SON.

14:58.667 --> 15:01.500
SHE WASN'T REALLY
THE MOTHER TYPE.

15:01.500 --> 15:03.100
SHE WAS MORE --

15:03.100 --> 15:04.900
HOW CAN I PUT THIS
DELICATELY? --

15:04.900 --> 15:07.500
A STRIPPER.

15:07.500 --> 15:09.600
MY MOM WAS A STRIPPER?

15:09.600 --> 15:11.233
THE BEST.

15:11.233 --> 15:13.200
DID YOU LOVE HER?

15:13.200 --> 15:15.600
I DID.
I DID LOVE HER.

15:15.600 --> 15:18.900
WASN'T ENOUGH
TO HOLD HER, THOUGH.

15:18.900 --> 15:20.967
NEITHER WAS I,
I GUESS.

15:20.967 --> 15:23.300
I WASN'T ENOUGH
TO HOLD<i>HER.</i>

15:23.300 --> 15:26.000
I WASN'T ENOUGH
TO HOLD<i>VIRNA.</i>

15:26.000 --> 15:28.867
NO!
YOU WERE ADORABLE.

15:28.867 --> 15:30.400
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:30.400 --> 15:34.734
YOU HAD THAT LITTLE BUTT
THAT VIRNA LOVED TO POWDER.

15:34.734 --> 15:38.667
WOMEN DID NOT FIND
<i>MY </i>BUTT ADORABLE, HOWEVER.

15:38.667 --> 15:42.934
THEY KICKED IT AROUND
PRETTY GOOD DURING MY LIFE.

15:42.934 --> 15:46.200
THE TRUTH IS,
YOU HAD A LOUSY MOTHER.

15:46.200 --> 15:47.900
AND A LOUSY FATHER.

15:47.900 --> 15:51.367
YOU COME FROM
A LONG LINE OF LOUSY, BOY.

15:51.367 --> 15:52.767
YEAH, I KNOW.

15:52.767 --> 15:54.500
[ SIGHS ]

15:54.500 --> 15:58.400
YOU GOT DEALT
A BAD HAND, SON.

15:58.400 --> 16:00.667
I'M SORRY ABOUT IT.

16:08.867 --> 16:11.400
YOU KNOW, THE MATTHEWS
OFFERED TO ADOPT ME.

16:11.400 --> 16:12.500
WHOA!
I KNOW.

16:12.500 --> 16:15.300
THAT SOUNDS
LIKE A SWEET DEAL!

16:15.300 --> 16:18.200
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

16:18.200 --> 16:21.033
IT DOESN'T GET ANY BETTER
THAN THE MATTHEWS.

16:21.033 --> 16:23.400
YOU'D BE TRADING<i>WAY</i>
UP ON THAT ONE.

16:23.400 --> 16:24.767
COME ON!
YOU'RE MY FATHER.

16:24.767 --> 16:26.734
I'M DEAD!

16:29.233 --> 16:32.934
LOOK, TAKE IT
FROM YOUR DEAD DAD.

16:32.934 --> 16:36.667
BECOME A MATTHEWS.
PUT IT TO BED.

16:36.667 --> 16:38.700
I ALWAYS THOUGHT
YOU WERE

16:38.700 --> 16:41.200
THE BLACK SHEEP
OF THE FAMILY.

16:41.200 --> 16:42.834
I WAS.
YOU WEREN'T.

16:42.834 --> 16:44.367
YOU STAYED.

16:44.367 --> 16:46.000
YOU RAISED ME.

16:46.000 --> 16:49.367
I CAME AND WENT.
I<i>TRIED--</i>

16:49.367 --> 16:51.700
Y-YOU DID A GOOD JOB
WITH ME, DAD.

16:51.700 --> 16:54.367
PEOPLE LIKE ME.
I EVEN HAVE FRIENDS.

16:54.367 --> 16:56.800
EVEN HAVE SOMEONE
WHO LOVES ME.

16:56.800 --> 16:58.400
WELL, HOLD ON TO HER.

16:58.400 --> 16:59.900
I WILL.

16:59.900 --> 17:02.400
JUST LIKE
I'M HOLDING ON TO YOU.

17:02.400 --> 17:05.000
WELL, [GRUNTS]

17:05.000 --> 17:07.100
WHY WOULD YOU
WANT TO DO THAT?

17:07.100 --> 17:09.000
BECAUSE I'M PROUD OF YOU!

17:09.000 --> 17:12.000
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO STARTED
TO TURN THIS FAMILY AROUND.

17:12.000 --> 17:13.200
YOU'RE PROUD OF ME?

17:13.200 --> 17:14.467
I COULDN'T BE PROUDER.

17:14.467 --> 17:16.300
[ Chuckling ]
AIN'T THAT A KICK?

17:16.300 --> 17:18.500
I TRIED TO TELL YOU
AT THE HOSPITAL.

17:18.500 --> 17:22.400
WELL, I-I-I COULDN'T REALLY
HEAR YOU, YOU KNOW.

17:22.400 --> 17:24.934
I WAS GOIN',
"OHH! OH! OOH!"

17:27.500 --> 17:29.200
I HEAR YOU NOW.

17:32.734 --> 17:36.400
THANK YOU...
FOR BEING MY FATHER.

17:38.834 --> 17:40.233
YOU LOVE ME, HUH?

17:40.233 --> 17:42.133
AIN'T<i>THAT </i>A KICK?

17:44.300 --> 17:46.200
WELL...

17:46.200 --> 17:49.133
MAYBE I CAN FINALLY
GET A LITTLE SLEEP.

18:00.100 --> 18:02.800
SHAWN?

18:02.800 --> 18:05.200
DID YOU DO
WHAT YOU NEEDED TO DO?

18:05.200 --> 18:06.900
YEAH, I DID.

18:12.000 --> 18:15.467
HI, MR. HUNTER.

18:15.467 --> 18:18.600
HOW YOU DOIN'?

18:18.600 --> 18:20.567
ME AND TOPANGA GOT MARRIED.

18:20.567 --> 18:22.467
I WISH YOU COULD'VE
BEEN THERE.

18:26.600 --> 18:29.000
SHAWN'S GONNA BE OKAY.

18:32.967 --> 18:34.600
I HOPE YOU'RE HAPPY.

18:38.033 --> 18:40.934
He is, Cor.

18:40.934 --> 18:43.033
Thanks.

18:51.200 --> 18:53.000
I'M SORRY...

18:53.000 --> 18:56.133
BUT I CAN'T BE A MATTHEWS.

18:56.133 --> 18:57.567
I UNDERSTAND.

18:57.567 --> 19:01.300
THE INVITATION
IS ALWAYS ON THE TABLE.

19:01.300 --> 19:02.834
THANK YOU.

19:02.834 --> 19:08.400
BUT I HAVE A FEELING
THERE'S TOO MUCH REPAIR WORK

19:08.400 --> 19:10.667
I GOTTA DO
FOR THE HUNTER CLAN.

19:10.667 --> 19:14.200
IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND,
YOU KNOW YOU HAVE FAMILY HERE.

19:14.200 --> 19:16.033
I KNOW.

19:16.033 --> 19:20.667
UM...LOOK. I'M SO SORRY
I RUINED YOUR PARTY.

19:20.667 --> 19:22.400
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

19:24.567 --> 19:26.500
OH-H-H-H-H!

19:31.600 --> 19:33.667
That is such
a stupid gift!

19:33.667 --> 19:35.667
Watch how mad Dad gets!

19:35.667 --> 19:38.100
"TO MY DAD."

19:38.100 --> 19:41.200
I'LL KEEP THIS
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

19:41.200 --> 19:43.934
THAT'S FROM BOTH OF US, DAD.
SEE THE --

19:46.200 --> 19:49.367
THERE IS ONE THING
YOU CAN DO FOR ME, THOUGH.

19:49.367 --> 19:50.600
NAME IT!

19:50.600 --> 19:53.400
YELL AT ME LIKE YOU YELL
AT CORY AND ERIC.

19:53.400 --> 19:55.000
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

19:55.000 --> 19:57.400
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.
REALLY GIVE IT TO ME!

19:57.400 --> 19:58.600
I'M NOT AFRAID.

19:58.600 --> 20:00.100
UH-OH!
Eric:
GIVE IT TO HIM!

20:00.100 --> 20:02.100
OH, YOU'RE NOT AFRAID,
HUH?

20:02.100 --> 20:05.367
WELL, MAYBE YOU SHOULD BE
A<i>LITTLE </i>AFRAID,

20:05.367 --> 20:08.200
BECAUSE I'M
A NAVY S.E.A.L.!

20:08.200 --> 20:09.567
THAT'S WHERE
I GOT THAT FROM!

20:09.567 --> 20:11.300
HE USED TO YELL AT ME
ALL THE TIME!

20:11.300 --> 20:14.200
YOU WANT
ANOTHER BEER, SHAWN?

20:14.200 --> 20:18.100
WHY DON'T YOU GO GET ONE
IN THE FRIDGE, HUH?

20:18.100 --> 20:21.000
SO MAYBE YOU CAN
LOSE AN ARM!

20:21.000 --> 20:22.500
OOH!

20:22.500 --> 20:23.967
HOW AM I DOING?

20:23.967 --> 20:26.467
GREAT.
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

20:26.467 --> 20:32.000
DON'T DO THESE THINGS ANYMORE.
IT SCARES YOUR FRIENDS.

20:32.000 --> 20:34.400
I KNOW IT SCARES ME.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.567
AND THEY LOVE YOU.

20:36.567 --> 20:38.700
YEAH. I DO.

20:38.700 --> 20:40.033
NEVER LEAVE.

20:40.033 --> 20:41.000
I WON'T.

20:42.934 --> 20:46.000
SOMEDAY, YOU MAY WANT
TO BUY A HOUSE,

20:46.000 --> 20:48.600
AND YOU'RE GOING TO
COME TO ME!

20:48.600 --> 20:50.500
I think
this is about us.

20:50.500 --> 20:51.700
IT'S A NICE TOUCH.

20:51.700 --> 20:54.133
WELL, I GOT NEWS
FOR YOU --

20:54.133 --> 20:55.867
GET A JOB!

20:55.867 --> 20:58.400
YES, SIR.
THANK YOU, SIR.

21:00.567 --> 21:02.500
You're welcome.
